<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
RATIFICATION of the Maastricht treaty in Ireland could create a
'constitutional nonsense' by overriding the Irish Supreme Court's decision
to allow a 14-year-old rape victim to terminate her pregnancy in Britain.
Mr Geoffrey Hoon, a UK Labour MEP, told the European Parliament's legal
affairs committee that Community legal experts should look into implications
of the special protocol attached to the treaty, which promises that EC law
will not affect the application of Ireland's constitutional 'right-to-life'
amendment.
The Irish Supreme Court has not yet given its reasons for setting aside a
