decisions on the right to travel abroad for abortions.
Mr Willi Rothley, German Socialist MEP who called for the debate, said the
Irish High Court decision had threatened EC treaty provisions guaranteeing
free provision of services throughout the EC.
But Mr Pat Cooney, an Irish lawyer and Fine Gael MEP, condemned fellow
deputies. 'It isn't up to the EC to harmonise the cultures, the religious
practices and the philosophies of member states,' he said.
