forward to reach 2,587, the high of the day, before light selling in the
dying minutes saw it rel-inquish some of the gain.
Turnover reached a poor 3,365 contracts, with March ending at 2,584, some 7
points above its estimated fair value premium to cash of about 6.
Dealers reported a more lively session in traded options, where turnover
rose to 30,827 lots. Barclays, which released figures, was the busiest stock
option, trading 1,869 contracts with the September 360 calls particularly
active.
