<HEADLINE>
FT  27 FEB 92 / International Company News: Shearson in Dollars 300m lawsuit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LOS ANGELES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Official Creditors Committee of bankrupt First Capital Holdings said it
had filed a Dollars 300m lawsuit on First Capital's behalf against Shearson
Lehman Brothers, the US securities house, and others alleging breaches of
fiduciary duty, gross mismanagement and manipulation, Reuter reports from
Los Angeles.
Shearson, a unit of American Express, is First Capital's controlling
shareholder.
The suit also charges Shearson with liability for the fraudulent transfer of
hundreds of millions of dollars of cash and assets.
Also named in the suit are Mr Robert Weingarten, former chief executive of
First Capital, Mr Peter Cohen, former chief executive of Shearson, and
others.
Shearson Lehman said it believed that the lawsuit was 'without merit'.
</TEXT>
