FT  27 FEB 92 / UK Company News: PE Kemp purchase and name change
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PE Kemp, the theatrical stage set designer in which Mr Jim Slater, the
property entrepreneur, has an interest, has acquired CR Pursehouse for
Pounds 3.2m in Kemp shares.
Kemp, which requested the suspension of its shares on February 13 pending
yesterday's announcement, is also proposing a capital reconstruction on the
basis of one new ordinary share for every five held and a change of name to
CRP Leisure.
CR Pursehouse is a construction and fitting company specialising in pubs and
leisure concerns.
