<HEADLINE>
FT  27 FEB 92 / UK Company News: 6% improvement to Pounds 9.1m at CMG
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Computer Management Group, a privately-held computing services company with
strengths in financial services and public utilities, last year shrugged off
the UK recession to record improved sales and profits.
Turnover for 1991 rose by 7 per cent to to Pounds 103m (Pounds 96.2m) while
pre-tax profits advanced by 6 per cent to Pounds 9.1m.
Earnings per share were 39.8p (37p), and a dividend of 13.1p (12.7p) is
recommended.
UK sales were flat at Pounds 39m but cost cutting measures ensured that the
UK activities made a profit of Pounds 600,000 last year compared with a loss
of Pounds 1m in 1990.
