<HEADLINE>
FT  27 FEB 92 / Algeria to get Dollars 1.5bn loans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCIS GHILES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A GROUP of eight international banks, led by Credit Lyonnais, yesterday
completed a Dollars 1.5bn commercial bank credit for Algeria after four
months of hard negotiations with some of their 130 peers.
The proceeds of this roll-over deal will help ease the repayment over five
to eight years of commercial bank loans which carry no guarantees from
western governments and which fall due up to March 31, 1993.
The initial agreement with the eight 'core' banks reached last October has
allowed Algerian banks to defer about Dollars 350m worth of principal
repayments owed to commercial banks in last quarter, 1991.
The accord also opens the way for a smaller disbursement of an Ecu400m
(Dollars 510m) loan guarantee agreed by the European Community in autumn. It
underlines lenders' willingness to do business with Algeria after
cancellation of the second round of the country's first multi-party
elections.
