up to four other carriers, but not American Airlines or Delta Airlines.
TAT also announced it was starting all-business class routes in Europe using
Paris as a hub. Services include Paris-Milan, from March 9, and
Paris-London, from March 30.
It is looking for a strong international partner following the disposal last
year by Air France, the French national airline, of its 35 per cent stake.
Mr Michel Marchais, founder of TAT, said he was prepared to sell 20 per cent
of his family's 72 per cent controlling interest to another airline.
