to the retention of the Union in its present form.
John Major's argument at the weekend that, collectively, England, Scotland,
Wales and Northern Ireland together are far greater than the sum of their
parts has to be taken with a large measure of salt. As the article points
out, it is largely the English who hold to a misplaced sense of superiority
on the world stage - something perpetuated by Mrs Thatcher, and subsequently
by Mr Major. Oh, the ether of power]
