FT  27 FEB 92 / Oil value down
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE VALUE of Britain's oil output fell in January for the third successive
month because of the continued weakness in world oil prices, according to
economists at Royal Bank of Scotland. The bank's oil index says earnings
fell even though production remained strong at more than 2m barrels a day.
