<HEADLINE>
FT  27 FEB 92 / UK construction orders rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK CONSTRUCTION orders rose slightly during the final three months of last
year thanks to strong performance from public-sector housing and housing
associations and from public works such as road building.
Private investment in residential, commercial and industrial property, fell
compared with the previous months.
Total orders, according to the Environment Department, were 1 per cent
higher than during July, August and September last year and 2 per cent
higher than in the final three months of 1990.
