mean that trade in cars can continue, but neither side will introduce a
duty-free quota system until the Commission and the Polish government have
found a solution.
France raised last-minute objections to Poland's plans at Tuesday's meeting
of EC internal market ministers, and was backed by the Commission and other
member states. An EC official said that Greece had also dropped its threat
to block the agreements with Czechoslovakia and Hungary.
