</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fisons has been cleared of questions regarding its 1990 accounts. The
Financial Reporting Review Panel had been examining criticisms that the
accounts did not disclose the basis of consolidation of the group accounts.
Fisons argued that consolidation requirements were defined in company
legislation and it did not need a separate statement of policy.
The panel stressed last month that this did not remove the requirement to
separately specify the accounting policies used.
